This was my very first interview that goes back to 2018. I procrastinated with the idea of starting a podcast for quite a lot of time, and, here it is, the episodes are coming in. It’s interesting to hear yourself talk, and see in what kind of state you were in a few years ago. 

I interviewed René Rannamägi, a young entrepreneur from Tallin, Estonia. A fellow explorer, lover of self-improvement, and all-around great positive guy.  

We talked about entrepreneurship, self-improvement, and the importance of learning by doing. This was the first one, it was very messy, so forgive my younger self. I hope you can enjoy and learn something valuable. 

Enjoy.


